+git-ssh-pull(1)
+===============
+v0.1, May 2005
+
+NAME
+----
+git-ssh-pull - Pulls from a remote repository over ssh connection
+
+
+
+SYNOPSIS
+--------
+'git-ssh-pull' [-c] [-t] [-a] [-d] [-v] [--recover] commit-id url
+
+DESCRIPTION
+-----------
+Pulls from a remote repository over ssh connection, invoking git-ssh-puig
+on the other end.
+
+OPTIONS
+-------
+-c::
+	Get the commit objects.
+-t::
+	Get trees associated with the commit objects.
+-a::
+	Get all the objects.
+-d::
+	Do not check for delta base objects (use this option
+	only when you know the remote repository is not
+	deltified).
+--recover::
+	Check dependency of deltified object more carefully than
+	usual, to recover after earlier pull that was interrupted.
+-v::
+	Report what is downloaded.
+
+
